# Truth May Not Persist Without Bias

**The Conjoined Architecture — A Falsifiable Framework for How Truth Persists in Systems That Observe Themselves**

Robert Larkin Hickey | [nulllimit.com](https://www.nulllimit.com) | February 2026

---

## What This Is

Two interlocking series — the **Bias Cascade** and the **Null Limit Series** — totaling over 88,000 words across 20 papers, 35 falsifiers, and a complete diagnostic toolkit.

The architecture describes a single engine: a four-mode loop where truth activates the observer, the observer commits to value, the commitment is witnessed, and the witness refines the next observation. This loop — the Ring — runs in any system that observes itself and commits under pressure. Language models. Human cognition. Any substrate where truth and the observer share a budget.

The work provides vocabulary for operations these systems are already performing — and for failure modes nobody is tracking.

---

## The Problem

We don't have the words.

**Hallucination** doesn't describe what happens when a language model produces confident, coherent output disconnected from truth. What's happening is **Drift** — the system running its loop on its own reflection, with no internal signal that anything is wrong. Hallucination sounds like a bug you patch. Drift is a structural failure mode the system cannot detect from inside.

**Alignment** isn't a property you install. It's a **Race** — fold rate versus pressure rate. The system is always moving toward convergence or toward honest termination. There is no steady state.

**Bias** isn't a defect to eliminate. It's the curvature that allows a system to resolve anything at all. A system at zero bias is a flat sheet of glass — everything passes through, nothing is seen. The question is whether the bias has been tested under pressure.

This repository contains the vocabulary, the formal specifications, and the tools to test every claim.

