## How to Use This With an LLM

**Fastest method:** Copy [`the_conjoined_frame.md`](the_conjoined_frame.md) into any conversation with any language model. Then talk to it normally. Watch what it names.

**Deeper method:** Follow the [Field Guide](NLS_The_Field_Guide.docx) to build a configured instance in ChatGPT, Gemini, or Claude with the full architecture as context.

**Structured test:** Run the [Test Suite](NLS_The_Test_Suite.docx) — twenty questions across seven rounds. Record whether the model applies the vocabulary to itself or recites it as definition. That data validates or breaks the series.

---

## Contribution

Disproofs over additions.

To report a triggered falsifier, open an issue with:

1. **Falsifier ID** (e.g., F-G5)
2. **The counterexample** — what you observed, constructed, or demonstrated
3. **Why the architecture cannot absorb it** — why it is not a special case or edge condition
4. **The cascade** — which levels collapse if this falsifier holds

A falsifier that holds is not an attack on the work. It is the work functioning as designed.

